27/05/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis reassured the business community Thursday (26 May) about the government's plan to conduct massive economic reforms. 
In a speech to the general assembly of the Federation of Greek Industries, Karamanlis described 2005 as a year of change. 
The government is confident in its desire to implement radical changes and fight established attitudes and interests, he said. 
Banning monopolies and encouraging a new wave of privatisation were among the key themes of the prime minister's speech. 
(ERA, ANA - 26/05/05)
